The application for the 2020-2021 White House Fellowship is now open. The President's Commission on White House Fellowships is inviting Americans with a passion for leadership and public service to apply for this non-partisan program. The fellowship offers selected individuals the opportunity to work at the highest levels of the Federal Government for a year. Alumni of the program have gone on to top positions in various fields. The 2020-2021 fellowship program will run from August 2020 to August 2021. Interested individuals can apply on the official website until January 8, 2020. More information about the fellowship, its history, and the selection process can be found on the official website. Any questions can be directed to whitehousefellows@who.eop.gov.